Description: Sherd of shoulder of closed pottery vessel, amphora or hydria; very micaceous light red-brown clay. Looping motifs on shoulder; two bands below. Incised inscription on shoulder
Curator's comments: Larger than the similar piece 1886,0401.958 and with much very small mica.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1886 / Naukratis. Part I., 1884-85 (pl. XXXIV, no. 639)
Bernand 1970 / Le Delta égyptien d'après les textes grecs, i: les confins libyques (p. 673, no. 317)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GO.023)
